title: High school senior dies after car strikes telephone pole in Peabody - Massachusetts news
text:
A teenager died Sunday night after his vehicle hit a telephone pole in Peabody, police said.
Peabody police received a call about the crash at 10:45 p.m. Emergency crews performed first aid on the driver before he was transported to the hospital, where he was later declared deceased, Captain Dennis Bonaiuto told Boston.com.
Related Link Get today’s headlines right in your inbox The accident is being investigated by the Massachusetts State Police reconstruction team, he said.
Advertisement - Continue Reading Below WCVB-TV identified the victim as Alex Vitale, a senior at Malden Catholic High School.
“It is with deep sadness that Malden Catholic mourns the loss of senior Alex Vitale,” the school said in a statement statement Monday morning. “The Malden Catholic Community joins together in prayer for Alex and his family.”
